Post-doctoral fellow / Engineer -  Predictive Analytics / Automatic Real
Time Segmentation of Web Visitors

*Place* : Universit=E9 de Haute-Alsace / Laboratoire MIPS (EA 2332),
Mulhouse, France
*Topic* : Automatic Real Time Segmentation of Web Visitors
*Collaboration* :  BeamPulse Corporation http://www.beampulse.com/fr/

Position for 18 months (two times 9 months), starting early 2015, salary
based on experience.

http://germain-forestier.info/stradi2015.htm

*Topic* : The conversion (or transformation) is the moment when a visitor
of a commercial website becomes a buyer of the products sold on the
website. Conversion rate is the ratio between the number of buyers and the
total number of visitors.
Increasing the turnover of a website by the sole increasing of traffic is
now over. Conversion Rate Optimization (CRO) is today the most promising
way for increasing the turnover of commercial websites.
The automatisation in real-time of segmentation of visitors aims at
increasing the conversion rate of commercial websites by influencing
directly the visitors present on a website at a given moment.
In the frame of a partnership between Beampulse, specialised in web visitor
behavior analysis, and the MIPS laboratory, specialist in behavior modeling
and data mining, we are currently offering a postdoctoral position (or
engineer) for 18 months (two times 9 months).
Her/his mission will be to integrate, adapt and program a new method for
behavioral segmentation (developed in our lab) into the BeamPulse software
platform.

Required skills :
- knowledge in application development (Java, Maven, Scrum)
- knowledge in web development (JavaScript, GWT, Spring)
- advanced knowledge in database management (NoSQL, Hadoop)
- knowledge on data mining (clustering, classification)

Expected skills :
- high level of autonomy, curiosity,  pro-active
- strong team working skills (including in remote settings)
- pragmatism and capacity to find solutions

Thanks for sending your application (CVs and motivation letter) to
pierre-alain.muller@uha.fr and germain.forestier@uha.fr with the prefix
[STRADI] in the subject of your email.

